~ Loop scope elision (a make-free repeat body runs in the parent env, no per-turn scope)
~ must not change any observable behavior. Prints FAIL on any mismatch.
make fails = 0

~ 1. a `make` inside the body still gets a FRESH scope each turn (no "already made" error)
repeat 3 times:
    make x = 5
    set x += 1

~ 2. a closure built in a make-free (elided) body still sees the right outer value
make base = 100
make fns = []
repeat 3 times:
    add(fns, task(): base)
make first = fns[0]
make last = fns[2]
when first() != 100 or last() != 100:
    set fails += 1

~ 3. a `make` in a NESTED `when` (its own scope) works though the loop body itself elides
make hits = 0
repeat 4 times:
    when yes:
        make y = 7
        set hits += y
when hits != 28:
    set fails += 1

~ 4. repeat while with a set-only (elided) body counts correctly
make n = 0
repeat while n < 1000:
    set n += 1
when n != 1000:
    set fails += 1

~ 5. stop still leaves the loop from an elided body
make seen = 0
repeat 10 times:
    set seen += 1
    when seen == 5:
        stop
when seen != 5:
    set fails += 1

~ 6. skip still skips the rest of a turn in an elided body
make evens = 0
make i = 0
repeat 10 times:
    set i += 1
    when i % 2 == 1:
        skip
    set evens += 1
when evens != 5:
    set fails += 1

when fails == 0:
    show "ok: loop scoping unchanged after elision (closures, nested makes, stop/skip)"
when fails != 0:
    show "FAIL: loop_scope fails=" + fails
